# API base for Server-Component fetchers (lib/api/*). Points at the ETL.
NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:3000

# Operator pages (the (investigation) route group) are gated by a Telegram
# session with the 'admin' role (ADMIN_TELEGRAM_IDS on the API). No separate
# operator auth provider — see md/runbook/telegram-auth.md.

# PostHog (client-side). Leave empty to keep analytics dormant in local dev.
# Use the project's Project API Key. Events route through the /ingest reverse
# proxy (next.config.ts) to dodge ad blockers — the PostHog region lives there,
# not here. EU project assumed; flip the hosts in next.config.ts for US.
NEXT_PUBLIC_POSTHOG_KEY=phc_xxx

# Telegram login — the bot's NUMERIC id (the part before ":" in TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN).
# Used by Telegram.Login.auth. The bot's domain must be registered via @BotFather
# /setdomain for the login popup to work (see md/runbook). Empty → login disabled.
NEXT_PUBLIC_TELEGRAM_BOT_ID=
